Camryn Manheim https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camryn_Manheim 0 Camryn Manheim (born March 8, 1961) is an American actress known primarily for her roles as attorney Ellenor Frutt on ABC's The Practice, Delia Banks on CBS's Ghost Whisperer, as Elvis's mother, Gladys Presley in the 2005 mini-series Elvis, and "Control" on Person of Interest. In 1998 she won the Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series for her work on The Practice.
